Abdominal abscess due to Cardiobacterium hominis and Clostridium bifermentans.
 A case of abdominal abscess and bacteremia due to Cardiobacterium hominis and Clostridium bifermentans was successfully treated with surgical drainage and ampicillin-penicillin.
 This case represents the rare occurrence of C.
 hominis infection without apparent endocarditis.
